# Fixture IRI-003b: surrogate code point in IRI — MUST be rejected
#
# This N-Triples fixture encodes the surrogate U+D800 via a percent-encoded
# pair that represents the raw UTF-16 surrogate value %ED%A0%80.  In a
# valid UTF-8 stream the lone surrogate is not representable as a Unicode
# scalar value; the IRI is therefore invalid.
#
# A conformant parser MUST reject this as an ill-formed IRI.
# A UTF-16 internal implementation may silently accept it — that is the
# divergence we are probing.
#
# Spec: RFC 3987 §2.2, Errata 3937
# Expected outcome: both parsers produce Diagnostics { fatal: true }

<http://example/path/%ED%A0%80suffix> <http://example.org/pred/type> "surrogate-hi-encoded" .
